  "prompt": "What are the adult signs of child sexual abuse?",
  "response": "There are several potential signs that an adult may have experienced childhood sexual abuse. Some common signs include:\n\n1. Mental health challenges\n- Depression\n- Anxiety\n- Post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD)\n- Low self-esteem\n\n2. Relationship difficulties\n- Trust issues\n- Intimacy problems\n- Difficulty maintaining healthy relationships\n\n3. Sexual and physical symptoms\n- Sexual dysfunction\n- Unexplained physical pain\n- Eating disorders\n- Sleep disturbances\n\n4. Emotional/behavioral signs\n- Substance abuse\n- Self-harm\n- Suicidal thoughts\n- Dissociation\n- Difficulty regulating emotions\n\n5. Psychological indicators\n- Hypervigilance\n- Flashbacks\n- Panic attacks\n- Difficulty with boundaries\n\nIf someone is experiencing these symptoms, professional counseling can help survivors process their experiences and heal. Resources like RAINN (Rape, Abuse & Incest National Network) offer support and guidance.",
